# tui/ code feedback

## Strengths
- Tidy, small, idiomatic. Each file has one responsibility, functions
  stay short. Matches the "feather" goal in AGENTS.md.
- Good use of stack-allocated fixed buffers (`var fixedBuf [256]byte`
  in `statusBarView`) and `strconv.AppendInt` instead of `fmt.Sprintf`
  — respects the no-`Sprintf` rule.
- Clean `Mode` enum, single `Model`, `Message` shape. Debug helpers
  neatly isolated in `debug.go`.
- Layout is described in a comment next to its functions — matches
  "comments beside implementation" rule.
- Layout now derived from `inputHeight`/`statusBarHeight` constants,
  so multi-line input growth is a one-line change.

## Issues / smells
1. `view.go:55` — `.fillLine` still allocates 3 slices per frame
   (one `emptyLine` shared + `screenBuf` itself + one input `line`).
   Better than the old 200/keystroke, but the real fix is the
   persistent flat buffer (#3 in the priority list).
2. `render.go:8` — `for i := range len(screen)` writes every row
   every frame (full repaint). No dirty-region tracking. Fine for
   now, but worth tracking.
3. `input.go:63` — resize handler clamps `cursorX` to `cols-1` but
   does not clamp to current `len(buf)`; cursor can float past
   content / get stuck off-buf on shrink. Also `cursorY` is never
   updated for multi-line, despite the comment saying "≥1 for
   multi-line".
4. `input.go:54` `renderInput` calls `Render`+`MoveCursor` even when
   nothing changed. Every keystroke does a full repaint (perf
   concern from #1/#2).
5. `input.go:98` `handleCtrl` only handles Ctrl-H/Backspace/Enter/
   Ctrl-J. Ctrl-C is handled in `HandleInput` as `KindQuit`, Ctrl-D
   returns via `KindEOF` — neither logs before exit except `KindQuit`
   prints `"CtrlC"`. Inconsistent.
6. `view.go:39-41` — status bar appends `cols`x`rows` using `int64`
   cast on each call; minor, but `strconv.AppendInt(buf, int64(...),
   10)` on every keystroke is wasteful. Wrap width inside a debug
   toggle.
7. `debug.go` `dbgInput`/`dbgModel` always log via `log.Printf` even
   in release. No build tag or `if debug {}` gate. Clutters logs in
   production.
8. `model.go:36` — `ModelName: "DeepSeek v4 (Pro)"` hardcoded; no
   config injection despite AGENTS.md mentioning swappable offline
   models (Qwen/DeepSeek). Should come from config.
9. `input.go:109` — `handleCSI` only handles Left/Right; up/down/
   Home/End/Delete/PageUp/PageDown are silently logged-and-dropped.
   At least `Home`/`End` trivial given current `buf`.
10. `view.go:78` — Truncation is byte-based; UTF-8 multi-byte chars
    (e.g. Italian accents, emoji) will be cut mid-rune and corrupt
    the terminal line. Needs `runewidth` / rune-aware truncation.

## Architectural gaps
- No scrolling / message history navigation (the `start` offset in
  `NewView` is a stub for this; needs `Model.scroll` + PageUp/PageDN).
- No streaming output / spinners for `ModeLoading` and
  `ModeStreaming`.
- No theming hook (AGENTS.md lists Theming as a goal); ANSI color
  codes are inlined in `statusBarView`.
- No tests.

# What to implement right now (priority order)

1. **Screen buffer reuse + dirty repaint** — keep a `[][]byte` on
   `Model` (and a reusable `blank []byte`), only grow/shrink on
   resize, reset content rows to `blank` without re-allocating.
   Removes per-keystroke garbage. Closes issue #1.
2. **Hardcode removal** — pass `ModelName` and status text in from
   config/main, not `NewModel`.
3. **Theming stub** — `type Theme struct{ StatusBarBg, StatusBarFg
   [3]byte }`, pass into `statusBarView`. Replaces raw
   `\033[38;2;0;0;0m\033[48;2;0;180;244m` literal.
4. **`Home`/`End`/`Delete` CSI** in `handleCSI` — trivial given
   existing cursor logic.
5. **Debug gating** — `dbgInput`/`dbgModel` behind a build tag
   (`//go:build debug`) or a `Model.debug bool`. Stops log spam in
   release.
6. **Rune-aware truncation** — swap byte slicing in `view.go:78`
   for a `runewidth`-based wrapper so UTF-8 renders cleanly.

Closed in this pass:
- Bounds & safety guard in `NewView` (TermRows<2 / TermCols<1) —
  no more `screenBuf[-1]` panic.
- `fillLine(..., '.')` debug dots replaced with spaces.
- `HandleEnter` now appends to `Messages` before clearing `buf`.
- Content area renders the last `chatAreaRows` messages bottom-up.
- `[]byte(Text[:clamp])` panic fixed via `min(TermCols, len(Text))`.
- Shadowed `len` variable renamed to `nMsg`.
- Layout derived from `inputHeight`/`statusBarHeight` constants via
  `chatAreaRows` / `inputRow` / `statusBarRow` — ready for
  multi-line input growth.
- Empty-input guard on Enter (skips blank sends).